{#- The serve WebUI shell. Markup lives here; CSS/themes are inlined (passed in as `themes_css` /
    `css`). The JS is the serve.*.mjs ES modules (BE-0247), served at their own routes and loaded via
    the entry module (`js_entry`); `js_modules` lists them for the modulepreload hints below. Keep
    this in sync with serve.css / the serve.*.mjs files. -#}
<!doctype html>
<html lang="en"><head><meta charset="utf-8"><meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
<title>bajutsu</title>
{#- The registered themes (built-in + drop-in) and the configured default, for the picker (BE-0191). -#}
<script>window.__bajutsuThemes={{ themes_json|safe }};window.__bajutsuDefaultTheme={{ default_theme_json|safe }};window.__bajutsuThemesWritable={{ themes_writable_json|safe }};</script>
{#- Resolve the theme before first paint so there is no dark→light flash on load: an explicit
    choice wins, else the configured ui.default_theme, else the OS scheme. -#}
<script>(function(){try{var t=localStorage.getItem('bajutsu-theme');if(!t)t=window.__bajutsuDefaultTheme||(matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme: light)').matches?'daylight':'midnight');document.documentElement.setAttribute('data-theme',t)}catch(e){}})();</script>
<style>{{ themes_css|safe }}{{ css|safe }}</style>
{#- Fetch every ES module in parallel rather than discovering them serially as imports resolve
    (BE-0247). A negligible nicety on localhost, but it keeps the request waterfall flat. -#}
{% for m in js_modules %}<link rel="modulepreload" href="/{{ m }}">
{% endfor %}</head>
<body>
<header>
  <div class="brandcol">
    <div class="brandrow">
      <span class="brand">bajutsu</span>
      {#- Running-tool identity (BE-0272): which build of bajutsu is serving this page — distinct
          from the config-provenance badge, which is about where the *config* came from. Sits quietly
          beside the title. Version is always shown; commit / branch / dirty are filled in by
          serve.core.mjs only when serve runs from a Git checkout and the caller may see them
          (admin-gated on a shared deployment). -#}
      <span class="appversion" id="appversion" data-testid="nav.app-version" hidden></span>
      {#- Settings / Edit / theme picker, grouped and right-aligned in .brandrow (beside the "bajutsu"
          title) rather than among .toptabs's config/view groups below — the button itself is a
          per-session/operator entry point, even though the Secrets tab inside the modal it opens does
          vary with the bound config. Settings and Edit sit to the left of the theme picker, in that
          order. -#}
      <div class="brandctrls">
        <button class="cfgbtn" id="opensettings" data-testid="nav.settings">Settings</button>
        <button class="cfgbtn" id="opentheme" title="Edit theme" data-testid="nav.open-theme">Edit</button>
        {#- Theme picker (BE-0191 unit 3): replaces the old two-state toggle with a native <select> listing
            every registered theme (built-in + drop-in), grouped by dark/light kind. Options are rendered
            from the same manifest exposed as window.__bajutsuThemes; the option value is the theme id, so a
            scenario selects a specific theme deterministically. serve.core.mjs seeds the selection from the
            applied theme and persists a change. A native select stays keyboard/screen-reader accessible and
            never overlaps the tiler/viewswitch controls at any width. -#}
        <label class="themepick" title="visual theme (follows your system by default)">
          <svg class="ico" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" aria-hidden="true"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="4"/><path d="M12 2v2M12 20v2M2 12h2M20 12h2M4.9 4.9l1.4 1.4M17.7 17.7l1.4 1.4M19.1 4.9l-1.4 1.4M6.3 17.7l-1.4 1.4"/></svg>
          <select id="theme" data-testid="nav.theme-picker" aria-label="visual theme">
            {%- for kind, klabel in [("dark", "Dark"), ("light", "Light")] %}
            {%- set group = themes | selectattr("kind", "equalto", kind) | list %}
            {%- if group %}
            <optgroup label="{{ klabel }}">
              {%- for t in group %}
              <option value="{{ t.id }}">{{ t.name }}</option>
              {%- endfor %}
            </optgroup>
            {%- endif %}
            {%- endfor %}
          </select>
        </label>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="toptabs">
      {#- Config controls come first so, once the header no longer fits one line, this (smaller)
          group is what stays on the shared first row while .viewtabs (the view tabs, a wider group)
          wraps onto its own second row as a whole — never interleaved button-by-button. -#}
      <div class="cfgctrls">
        <span class="cfgname" id="cfgname" data-testid="nav.config-name"></span>
        <button class="cfgbtn" id="opencfg" data-testid="nav.open-config">Open config</button>
        <button class="cfgbtn" id="viewcfg" data-testid="nav.view-config" hidden>View</button>
        {#- Project hub switcher (BE-0225 unit 4): next to the config viewer. A native <select> lists the
            org's registered projects; changing it activates one, rebinding the live config so every tab
            runs against it. It stays hidden until a hub exists (more than one project to switch between),
            so a single-config `serve` looks exactly as before. Adding / removing / inspecting projects
            moved to the top-level Projects page (BE-0275); this quick-switch control stays. -#}
        <select class="projectsw" id="projectsw" data-testid="nav.projects" aria-label="active project" hidden></select>
      </div>
      <div class="viewtabs">
        <button class="toptab active" data-view="record" data-testid="nav.record">Record</button>
        <button class="toptab" data-view="replay" data-testid="nav.replay">Replay</button>
        <button class="toptab" data-view="crawl" data-testid="nav.crawl">Crawl</button>
        <button class="toptab" data-view="author" data-testid="nav.author">Author</button>
        <button class="toptab" data-view="stats" data-testid="nav.stats">Stats</button>
        <button class="toptab" data-view="flaky" data-testid="nav.flaky">Flaky</button>
        <button class="toptab" data-view="usage" data-testid="nav.usage">Usage</button>
        <button class="toptab" data-view="coverage" data-testid="nav.coverage">Coverage</button>
        <button class="toptab" data-view="metrics" data-testid="nav.metrics" hidden>Metrics</button>
        {#- Projects page (BE-0275): the hub's home. Unlike the switcher + Metrics tab (a real hub only),
            it shows for any project count so a single-config `serve` can grow into a hub from its Add
            form; serve.core.mjs (loadProjects) reveals it whenever there is a project to manage. -#}
        <button class="toptab" data-view="projects" data-testid="nav.projects-view" hidden>Projects</button>
        {#- Trash (BE-0239): soft-deleted runs, restorable within the retention window. Always offered —
            run deletion is available on every deployment. -#}
        <button class="toptab" data-view="trash" data-testid="nav.trash">Trash</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</header>

<!-- ===== Record: author a scenario from a natural-language goal ===== -->
<main id="view-record" data-testid="view.record" data-pane="form">
  <!-- Per-view switcher (shown only at the phone tier): brings one stacked pane to full width. -->
  <div class="viewswitch" role="tablist" data-testid="record.switch">
    <button class="vstab active" data-pane="form">Form</button>
    <button class="vstab" data-pane="log">Progress</button>
    <button class="vstab" data-pane="yaml">Output</button>
  </div>
  <div class="left" data-pane="form">
    <!-- Claude-reachability gate (BE-0101): shown disabled with an inline explanation when Claude is
         unreachable, so `record` degrades gracefully instead of failing only on click. Lives inside
         the controls pane so the desktop tile layout (which replaces the view's direct children)
         keeps it. -->
    <div class="ai-gate" id="rec-aigate" data-testid="record.ai-gate" hidden></div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="panel" id="panel-record">
        <label>Goal (natural language)</label>
        <textarea id="rec-goal" data-testid="record.goal" class="goal" placeholder="e.g. increment the counter twice and check it reads 2"></textarea>
        <label>Target</label><select id="rec-target" data-testid="record.target"></select>
        <label class="iosonly">Device</label>
        <div class="row iosonly" style="align-items:flex-end">
          <div><select id="rec-device"></select></div>
          <div style="flex:0 0 auto"><button class="refresh" id="rec-simrefresh" title="refresh devices">&#8635;</button></div>
        </div>
        <!-- Readiness (BE-0148): the same doctor pre-run check as the Replay panel, so authoring
             a scenario can start from a known-runnable, addressable app. Read-only and AI-free. -->
        <div class="doctor" data-testid="record.doctor">
          <div class="hhead"><span>Readiness</span><button class="refresh" id="recdr-check" title="check readiness" data-testid="record.doctor-check">Check</button></div>
          <div class="status" id="recdr-status"></div>
          <div class="grade-badge" id="recdr-grade" data-testid="record.doctor-grade" hidden></div>
          <div class="dr-checks" id="recdr-checks"></div>
          <div class="au-audit" id="recdr-findings" hidden></div>
        </div>
        <label>Save as</label>
        <input id="rec-name" type="text" placeholder="generated.yaml — leave blank to default">
        <div class="subhint">The recorded scenario is written under the scenarios dir, so it shows up in the <b>Replay</b> tab to run. Blank defaults to <code>generated.yaml</code>; if the name already exists, the run's date-time is appended (e.g. <code>generated-20260613-153045.yaml</code>) so nothing is overwritten.</div>
        <div class="checks iosonly">
          <label><input type="checkbox" id="rec-erase"> erase device first
            <span class="hint">Wipe the simulator before authoring (record's default) so the app starts from onboarding. Uncheck to author against the app's current state.</span></label>
          <label><input type="checkbox" id="rec-nodismiss"> disable alert-dismiss
            <span class="hint">The alert guard (Claude vision) dismisses unexpected system prompts while authoring; on by default (needs ANTHROPIC_API_KEY). Check to force it off.</span></label>
        </div>
        <div class="checks webonly">
          <label><input type="checkbox" id="rec-headed" data-testid="record.headed"> show browser (headed)
            <span class="hint">Author against a visible Chromium window in slow-motion so you can watch the agent explore, instead of the default headless browser. The window opens on the machine running <code>serve</code>.</span></label>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="gutter" data-var="--rec-left" data-min="260" data-max="640"></div>
  <div class="rec-stack">
    <div class="card logpanel" data-pane="log">
      <button class="run" id="rec-go" data-testid="record.generate" data-idle="Generate scenario">Generate scenario</button>
      <button class="stop" id="rec-stop" hidden>Stop</button>
      <div class="status" id="rec-status"></div>
      <pre class="out" id="rec-out" data-empty="Enter a goal and press Generate to watch the agent author it, turn by turn."></pre>
    </div>
    <div class="gutter row" data-var="--rec-top" data-min="120" data-max="700"></div>
    <div class="card yamlpanel" id="rec-yamlpanel" data-pane="yaml">
      <div class="yamlhead">
        <span class="ttl">Generated scenario</span>
        <span class="muted" id="rec-yamlinfo" style="font-size:.8em"></span>
        <div class="yaml-actions">
          <button class="savebtn" id="rec-save" data-testid="record.save" disabled>Save</button>
          <button class="savebtn" id="rec-run" data-testid="record.run" data-idle="▶ Run" disabled>▶ Run</button>
          <button class="stop" id="rec-runstop" hidden>Stop</button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <textarea id="rec-yaml" data-testid="record.yaml" class="yaml" placeholder="The recorded scenario YAML appears here once authoring finishes — edit and Save, then Run it here (or in the Replay tab)."></textarea>
    </div>
    <!-- Run result: an inline panel (same tiling mechanism as the panels above) holding only the
         report, shown when ▶ Run is pressed and dismissable with its X. The live run log streams to
         the Progress console above, like Generate. Hidden by default; the desktop tiler adds/removes
         it as an optional pane, and at the phone tier the `hidden` attribute + Output tab govern it. -->
    <div class="card rec-report-panel" id="rec-reportpanel" data-pane="yaml" hidden>
      <div class="yamlhead">
        <span class="ttl">Run result</span>
        <span class="muted" id="rec-runstatus" style="font-size:.8em"></span>
        <button class="fsclose" id="rec-runclose" data-testid="record.run-close" style="margin-left:auto">&#10005;</button>
      </div>
      <div id="rec-report" data-testid="record.run-report"></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</main>

<!-- Human handoff (BE-0179): a "needs human" turn pauses the record. Shown as a modal (not a pane)
     so it can't be missed below the fold — the human must answer to resume: supply a value, confirm
     they operated the device, or cancel. No backdrop dismiss; the buttons are the only exits. -->
<div class="modal" id="rec-handoffmodal" data-testid="record.handoff-modal" hidden>
  <div class="fsbox" role="dialog" aria-modal="true" aria-labelledby="rec-handoff-heading">
    <div class="fshead"><span class="ttl" id="rec-handoff-heading">✋ Human handoff</span></div>
    <div class="rec-handoff-body">
      <div id="rec-handoff-reason"></div>
      <div class="muted" id="rec-handoff-screen" style="font-size:.85em"></div>
      <img id="rec-handoff-shot" alt="the screen the record paused on" hidden />
      <label class="muted" for="rec-handoff-value" style="font-size:.85em">Supply a value (e.g. a one-time password), or operate the device yourself and resume:</label>
      <input id="rec-handoff-value" data-testid="record.handoff-value" type="text" placeholder="value to supply" />
      <div class="rec-handoff-actions">
        <button id="rec-handoff-send" data-testid="record.handoff-send">Supply value</button>
        <button id="rec-handoff-acted" data-testid="record.handoff-acted">I did it — resume</button>
        <button id="rec-handoff-cancel" data-testid="record.handoff-cancel">Cancel</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ===== Replay: run a scenario and view its report ===== -->
<main id="view-replay" data-testid="view.replay" data-pane="form" hidden>
  <div class="viewswitch" role="tablist" data-testid="replay.switch">
    <button class="vstab active" data-pane="form">Form</button>
    <button class="vstab" data-pane="log">Log</button>
    <button class="vstab" data-pane="report">Report</button>
  </div>
  <div class="left" data-pane="form">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="tabs">
        <button class="tab active" data-tab="run" data-testid="replay.tab-run">Run</button>
        <button class="tab" data-tab="history" id="histtab" data-testid="replay.tab-history">History</button>
      </div>
      <div class="panel" id="panel-run" data-testid="replay.panel-run">
        <label>Scenario</label>
        <select id="scn" data-testid="replay.scenario"></select><div class="names" id="names" data-testid="replay.scenario-info"></div>
        <!-- See what you're about to run (BE-0273): a read-only view of the selected scenario's
             raw YAML + runner-parsed steps. Enabled once a scenario is picked; no run required. -->
        <button class="cfgbtn" id="viewscn" data-testid="replay.view-scenario" disabled>View scenario</button>
        <!-- Determinism audit badge (BE-0145): the selected scenario's static stability grade. -->
        <div class="grade-badge" id="scn-grade" data-testid="replay.grade" hidden></div>
        <label>Target</label><select id="target" data-testid="replay.target"></select>
        <div class="row iosonly"><div><label>Workers</label><input id="workers" type="number" min="1" value="1"></div></div>
        <div class="hhead iosonly" data-testid="replay.simulators"><span>Simulators</span><button class="refresh" id="simrefresh" title="refresh devices">&#8635;</button></div>
        <div class="sims iosonly" id="sims"></div>
        <div class="subhint iosonly">Pick the simulators to run on &mdash; shut-down ones are booted (and waited for) before the run. Pick two or more (Workers auto-tracks the count) to run the scenarios in parallel across them: each device gets its own network capture, video / device log, and setLocation / push. None picked = the already-booted device.</div>
        <!-- Readiness (BE-0148): shells out to the same doctor checks the CLI runs — tool/device
             runnability plus the current screen's convention score — so a user can answer "is my
             environment ready, and is my app addressable?" before pressing Run. Read-only and
             AI-free; it never gates the run. The checks come back backend-appropriate, so the
             panel shows for iOS and web alike (simulator-only form controls above stay .iosonly). -->
        <div class="doctor" data-testid="replay.doctor">
          <div class="hhead"><span>Readiness</span><button class="refresh" id="dr-check" title="check readiness" data-testid="replay.doctor-check">Check</button></div>
          <div class="status" id="dr-status"></div>
          <div class="grade-badge" id="dr-grade" data-testid="replay.doctor-grade" hidden></div>
          <div class="dr-checks" id="dr-checks"></div>
          <div class="au-audit" id="dr-findings" hidden></div>
        </div>
        <div class="checks iosonly">
          <label><input type="checkbox" id="erasedev"> erase device first
            <span class="hint">Wipe the whole simulator (simctl erase &mdash; all apps, data, settings) before each scenario. Off (default) leaves it to each scenario's <code>preconditions.erase</code>; the app is reinstalled fresh either way.</span></label>
          <label><input type="checkbox" id="nodismiss"> disable alert-dismiss
            <span class="hint">The alert guard is on by default: Claude vision dismisses unexpected system prompts (Save Password, notification permission) that a scenario's own steps can't see or tap (needs ANTHROPIC_API_KEY). Check to force it off for this run; a scenario can also set <code>alertHandling</code> itself.</span></label>
        </div>
        <div class="checks webonly">
          <label><input type="checkbox" id="headed" data-testid="replay.headed"> show browser (headed)
            <span class="hint">Run in a visible Chromium window in slow-motion so you can watch each step, instead of the default headless browser. The window opens on the machine running <code>serve</code> (so this is for a local server).</span></label>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="panel" id="panel-history" data-testid="replay.panel-history" hidden>
        <div class="hhead"><span>Past runs</span><button class="refresh" id="refresh" title="refresh">&#8635;</button></div>
        <!-- Drilldown filter (BE-0241): shown only when the Stats dashboard deep-linked here with a
             run set; "clear" drops back to the full history. -->
        <div class="histfilter" id="histfilter" data-testid="replay.history-filter" hidden><span id="histfilter-label"></span> · <button type="button" class="linklike" id="histfilter-clear">clear</button></div>
        <!-- Bulk delete (BE-0239): shown whenever the list has rows; "select all" arms it, and the
             per-row checkboxes feed the count. Delete stays disabled until at least one run is picked. -->
        <div class="bulkbar" id="histbulk" data-testid="replay.bulk-bar" hidden>
          <label class="bulksel"><input type="checkbox" id="histbulk-all" data-testid="replay.bulk-all"> select all</label>
          <span class="bulkcount" id="histbulk-count"></span>
          <button type="button" class="cfgbtn prjremove" id="histbulk-del" data-testid="replay.bulk-delete" disabled>Delete selected</button>
          <button type="button" class="linklike" id="histbulk-clear" data-testid="replay.bulk-clear">clear</button>
        </div>
        <ul class="history" id="history"></ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="gutter" data-var="--rep-left" data-min="260" data-max="560"></div>
  <div class="card logpanel" data-pane="log">
    <button class="run" id="go" data-testid="replay.run" data-idle="Run">Run</button>
    <button class="stop" id="stop" hidden>Stop</button>
    <div class="status" id="status"></div>
    <pre class="out" id="out" data-empty="Run a scenario to see its output here."></pre>
    <!-- codegen (BE-0137): export the selected scenario as a native test, right where it just ran. -->
    <div class="codegen-bar">
      <select class="codegen-emit" id="rp-emit" data-testid="replay.emit" aria-label="codegen destination" title="codegen destination"></select>
      <button class="savebtn" id="rp-codegen" data-testid="replay.codegen">Generate code</button>
    </div>
    <div class="codegen-panel" id="rp-codegen-panel" hidden>
      <div class="codegen-head">
        <span class="ttl" id="rp-codegen-title" data-testid="replay.codegen-filename">Generated code</span>
        <span class="codegen-actions">
          <button class="savebtn" id="rp-codegen-copy" data-testid="replay.codegen-copy">Copy</button>
          <button class="savebtn" id="rp-codegen-download" data-testid="replay.codegen-download">Download</button>
          <button class="savebtn" id="rp-codegen-close" data-testid="replay.codegen-close">Close</button>
        </span>
      </div>
      <pre class="codegen-code" id="rp-codegen-code" data-testid="replay.codegen-code" tabindex="0"></pre>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="gutter" data-var="--rep-mid" data-min="220" data-max="640"></div>
  <div class="report" id="report" data-testid="replay.report" data-pane="report"><div class="empty">Run a scenario to see its report here.</div></div>
</main>

<!-- ===== Crawl: explore the app breadth-first and map its screens live ===== -->
<main id="view-crawl" data-testid="view.crawl" data-pane="form" hidden>
  <div class="viewswitch" role="tablist" data-testid="crawl.switch">
    <button class="vstab active" data-pane="form">Form</button>
    <button class="vstab" data-pane="graph">Graph</button>
    <button class="vstab" data-pane="plan">Plan</button>
    <button class="vstab" data-pane="console">Console</button>
  </div>
  <div class="left" data-pane="form">
    <!-- Claude-reachability gate (BE-0101); see the record view above. -->
    <div class="ai-gate" id="crawl-aigate" data-testid="crawl.ai-gate" hidden></div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="tabs">
        <button class="tab active" data-tab="crawlform" data-testid="crawl.tab-form">Form</button>
        <button class="tab" data-tab="crawlhistory" id="crawl-histtab" data-testid="crawl.tab-history">History</button>
      </div>
      <div class="panel" id="panel-crawl">
        <label>Target</label><select id="crawl-target" data-testid="crawl.target"></select>
        <div class="row" style="align-items:flex-end">
          <div><label>Workers</label><input id="crawl-workers" data-testid="crawl.workers" type="number" min="1" value="1"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="subhint webonly">Crawl this many browser processes at once, sharing one screen map (BE-0077): independent branches explore in parallel and the AI guide's round-trips overlap, so the map builds faster. Each worker is its own browser, so one that wedges is relaunched without sinking the crawl. 1 = a single browser.</div>
        <div class="hhead iosonly"><span>Simulators</span><button class="refresh" id="crawl-simrefresh" title="refresh devices">&#8635;</button></div>
        <div class="sims iosonly" id="crawl-sims"></div>
        <div class="subhint iosonly">Pick the simulators to crawl on &mdash; shut-down ones are booted (and waited for) first. Pick two or more (Workers auto-tracks the count) to crawl across them in parallel: they share one screen map, so independent branches explore at once and the AI guide's round-trips overlap (BE-0064). None picked = the already-booted device.</div>
        <div class="row">
          <div><label>Max screens</label><input id="crawl-maxscreens" data-testid="crawl.max-screens" type="number" min="1" value="50"></div>
          <div><label>Max steps</label><input id="crawl-maxsteps" data-testid="crawl.max-steps" type="number" min="1" value="200"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="subhint">Crawl explores the app breadth-first, discovering screens and the transitions between them &mdash; a discovery tool, never a pass/fail gate. It is AI-driven: the engine (screen identity, transitions, crashes) is always deterministic, while the <b>AI</b> proposes <i>what to try</i> &mdash; richer operations and realistic inputs to enable controls whose precondition isn't obvious. The AI backend is the one chosen in <b>Settings</b> &mdash; the Anthropic API, Amazon Bedrock, or the Claude Code CLI. Stops at the first of Max screens / Max steps.</div>
        <div class="checks iosonly">
          <label><input type="checkbox" id="crawl-erase"> erase device first
            <span class="hint">Wipe the simulator before crawling so the app starts from onboarding. Off by default — the app is reinstalled fresh either way; check to also wipe all apps / data / settings first.</span></label>
          <label><input type="checkbox" id="crawl-nodismiss"> disable alert-dismiss
            <span class="hint">The alert guard (Claude vision) dismisses unexpected OS prompts so they aren't read as crashes; on by default (uses the AI provider set in Settings &mdash; ANTHROPIC_API_KEY for Anthropic, or AWS credentials for Bedrock). Check to force it off.</span></label>
        </div>
        <div class="checks webonly">
          <label><input type="checkbox" id="crawl-headed" data-testid="crawl.headed"> show browser (headed)
            <span class="hint">Crawl a visible Chromium window in slow-motion so you can watch the exploration, instead of the default headless browser. The window opens on the machine running <code>serve</code>.</span></label>
        </div>
        <button class="run" id="crawl-go" data-testid="crawl.start" data-idle="Start crawl">Start crawl</button>
        <button class="stop" id="crawl-stop" hidden>Stop</button>
        <div class="status" id="crawl-status"></div>
      </div>
      <!-- History (BE-0180): past crawls, keyed on the screenmap.json each one streams. Selecting one
           reopens its screen map read-only via the existing loadGraph — no re-crawl, no verdict. -->
      <div class="panel" id="crawl-panel-history" data-testid="crawl.panel-history" hidden>
        <div class="hhead"><span>Past crawls</span><button class="refresh" id="crawl-refresh" title="refresh">&#8635;</button></div>
        <!-- Bulk delete (BE-0239): mirrors the Replay history bulk bar. -->
        <div class="bulkbar" id="crawlbulk" data-testid="crawl.bulk-bar" hidden>
          <label class="bulksel"><input type="checkbox" id="crawlbulk-all" data-testid="crawl.bulk-all"> select all</label>
          <span class="bulkcount" id="crawlbulk-count"></span>
          <button type="button" class="cfgbtn prjremove" id="crawlbulk-del" data-testid="crawl.bulk-delete" disabled>Delete selected</button>
          <button type="button" class="linklike" id="crawlbulk-clear" data-testid="crawl.bulk-clear">clear</button>
        </div>
        <ul class="history" id="crawl-history" data-testid="crawl.history"></ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="card crawl-graph-panel" data-pane="graph">
    <div class="crawlhead">
      <span class="ttl">Screen map</span>
      <span class="crawlcounts" id="crawl-counts"></span>
      <!-- Shown only while a historical run is open (BE-0180), to keep a past map from reading as live. -->
      <span class="pastbadge" id="crawl-pastbadge" data-testid="crawl.past-badge" hidden></span>
      <!-- Continue a past run's remaining frontier (BE-0181): shown for an open past run that still has
           untried operations. Clicking it leaves the read-only history view and continues exploring live. -->
      <button class="pastcontinue" id="crawl-continue" data-testid="crawl.continue" hidden></button>
